name: Megan McKelvey
text: We’ve tried a few different baked goods that were all delicious! The staff is very friendly. We love Marta’s!

name: Karen T
text: I was frustrated 2 months before my wedding, I could not find someone who can prepare my kosher cake. Justin from Marta's bakery  was willing to do her first kosher cake, she came to our kitchen and learnt everything about it. She was beyond of her job, she brought the ingredients a day before and she helped us to decorate the cake and find special ingredients we requested in order to keep it kosher. Everybody loved it. She also figured out to find the birds I could not have the time to find it and did everything for a good price, punctuality and quality. Thanks Justin.

name: Ammar Shaqar
text: Marta's Bakery is lovely!! It has a large selection of homemade casseroles that are out of this world. The Martha Bakery employees are helpful, answered all my questions, didn't rush me, & were kind. The bakery is well organized, clean, and the food items are clearly marked with simple cooking directions!

name: Crestline Sugar
text: LooovveeeMartas! Shes a community stale- yeast rolls are like my grandmother used to make. Santa Fe soup, veg beef soup, and raspberry congealed salad- All unbelievable!

name: Cameron al Shaqar
text: Today was my first visit to Marta's Bakery but it won't be my last. The bakery is easy to find, has great parking, & the nicest customer service. More importantly, the food is divine.

name: Cody Spray
text: Awesome food! Very affordable! Marta and her staff are always friendly and accommodating. Did I mention the food is awesome?

name: Juston Dailey
text: amazing place always so fresh best pecan pie and delicious soft cakes

name: Tiffany
text: I ordered a birthday cake for my son. This was the worst professsional cake I have ever tasted. A birthday cake supposed to be light and fluffy this was nothing of the sort. The cake was thick, dry and wasn't completely done in the center. I could have done a better job on the cake myself.

name: Jan Grill
text: The chicken tetrazinni is awesome!

name: Angela_ downs
text: You have to try Marta's cheese straws, they are excellent!!

name: Anthony Hodo
text: Great food and workers, nothing beats their brownies.

name: Brian W. Kittrell
text: Great, friendly service. Fantastic pies and cheese straws.

name: Zandra Lopez-Jones
text: I called talking in Spanish thinking it was a Hispanic Bakery. They lady who answered hung up on me.. I thought well maybe the called dropped - i called again the lady picked up and told me we don't speak Spanish and hung up on me and did not give me the chance to explain I speak English... I called again and talked in English and told her I was the one who called speaking in Spanish and you hung up on me... she stated we don't speak Spanish and I told her you did not give me time to answer and say I speak English she did not apologize and was very rude and disrespectful... this company does not deserve my business especially my money...

name: michael hill
text: Very good food beats cooking quick and easy

name: Ada McBride
text: Delicious yeast rolls! Cheese straws too!

name: Ralphy mguilacutty
text: Hands down the best bakery in Birmingham!

name: Joan Newell
text: Loved bakery.

name: Noah Morgan
text: Good experience

name: Susan mcgriff
text: It's a cooking class

name: Ellen W
text: Been picking blueberries here for 18 yrs

name: Kim Hollingsworth
text: Always love going to Crafts Blueberry Farms.  A yearly tradition with my mom.
